how to deploy image using imperative method
kubectl create deployment abcd --image=image-path 

to expose the deploymen we need to use the command 
kubectl expose deployment --type=Loadbalancer --port=8080

kubectl service service-name

kubectl scale deploymet/nameofdeployment --replicas=3

how to update the image 
kubectl set image deployment/appname nameofapplication=dockerhubimage name

how to rollout using command

kubectl rollout status deployment/first-appname

kubectl rollout undo deployment/first-appname


imperative vs declarative 

